PEDIPALPS (
Fig. 3A
). Trochanter with strong ventral apophysis. Femur dorsally convex without pronounced dorsal keel or tubercles, with ventral row of ten well-formed setiferous tubercles and a mesodistal process. Patella with mesal keel. Shallow slit along tibia mesal surface, separating dorsal and ventral sides.

COLOR (
Fig. 1
). Body and appendages background Strong Orange Yellow (68) mottled in Dark Yellowish Brown (78), ladder mask Pale Greenish Yellow (104). Pedipalpus as well as trochanters and tarsomeres of legs Light Greenish Yellow (101).
